body:
This PR allows us to turn on TurbulenceConvection, and uses it for a new job.

I've been using this to run:

```julia
using Revise
include("examples/hybrid/cli_options.jl")
(s, parsed_args) = parse_commandline();

parsed_args["config"] = "column";
parsed_args["FLOAT_TYPE"] = "Float64";
parsed_args["moist"] = "equil";
parsed_args["turbconv"] = "edmf";
parsed_args["ode_algo"] = "Euler";
parsed_args["energy_name"] = "rhotheta";
parsed_args["split_ode"] = false;
parsed_args["job_id"] = "edmf_single_column";
parsed_args["dt"] = "1secs";
parsed_args["t_end"] = "1mins";

include("examples/hybrid/driver.jl")
```

Some remaining items are (for follow-up PRs)
 - Synchronizing names
 - More refactoring / synchronizing types

I think that this is finished and ready. It's pretty clunky at the moment, due to many edmf initialization details that we should probably improve. But I think it'd be beneficial to get something working and then we can make things look better while maintaining results.

This PR
- fixes a bug in save to disk function for dry case;
- adds RH into moist simulation outputs;
- modifies remap_pipeline to add diagnostics into nc files;
- rename cloud_water -> cloud_liquid.
